apertium-separable
------------------------------------------
Lttoolbox provides a module for reordering separable/discontiguous multiwords
and processing them in the pipeline. Multiwords are manually written in an
additional xml-format dictionary.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.6-1
  libgcc1-9.3.0-2
  liblttoolbox3_3.5_1-3.5.2-1bl1
  libstdc++6-9.3.0-2
  libxml2-2.9.9-2
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  gcc-g++-9.3.0-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-separable

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-separable/archive/v0.3.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack apertium-separable-0.3.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./apertium-separable-0.3.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/apertium-separable-0.3.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/apertium-separable-0.3.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(apertium-separable)
  /usr/bin/lsx-comp.exe
  /usr/bin/lsx-proc.exe
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/apertium-separable.pc
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/apertium-separable.README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/readme.md

